g the plexus-archiver as part of Maven, specifically use by the dependency-maven-plugin. \n\nI have extended UnArchiver to allow specification of include/exclude patterns, and could provide a patch for plexus-archive.  Right now it uses org.codehaus.maven.model.PatternSets, but it could also be implemented with generic include/exclude lists to avoid the Maven dependency.  What is not as straightforward is whether to just modify the UnArchiver interface to add this capability (thereby breaking other implementations of UnArchiver outside of plexus-archiver), or whether a new specialized interface should be written.\n\nHere's more discussion on the Maven user list:  http://www.nabble.com/-m2-Unarchive-selected-files-dirs-t918009.html\n","priority":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/priority/3","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/priorities/major.png","name":"Major","id":"3"},"duedate":null,"issuelinks":[{"id":"28720","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issueLink/28720","type":{"id":"10000","name":"Duplicate","inward":"is duplicated by","outward":"duplicates","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issueLinkType/10000"},"outwardIssue":{"id":"47604","key":"PLXCOMP-58","self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issue/47604","fields":{"summary":"Add filter ability to plexus-archiver","status":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/statuses/closed.png","name":"Closed","id":"6"},"priority":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/priority/3","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/priorities/major.png","name":"Major","id":"3"},"issuetype":{"self":"http://jira.codehaus.org/rest/api/2/issuetype/2","id":"2","description":"A new feature of the product, which has yet to be developed.","iconUrl":"http://jira.codehaus.org/images/icons/issuetypes/newfeatu